    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="letter">
                <pb n="1" facs="Edgeworth_Geneve_33_2_1816_05_06_page01.jpg"/>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline> 
                     <date when="1816-05-06">6. May 16</date><note>41</note>
                     <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Edgeworthstown_IE">Edgeworthstown</placeName></dateline>
                
                        My Dear Sir</opener>
                        <p>
                        I trouble you with<lb/>
                        a line to express my satis-<lb/>
                        -faction upon the [insertion]temporary[/insertion] failure of<lb/>
                        Sir Samuel Romillys bill.<lb/>
                        The admirable speech of<lb/>
                        the master of the Rolls would<lb/>
                        never have been published if<lb/>
                        there had not been a party<lb/>
                        opposition - Such a collect<lb/>
                        -ion of miserable stuff as fell<lb/>
                        from Gibbs &amp; Plumer I never<lb/>
                        read! - My friend Giddy has<lb/>
                        fallen off prodigiously - .<lb/>
                        The production of the Judges against<lb/>
                        the bill was as feeble an attempt<lb/>
                        as could be made - It dared not<lb/>
                    
                        <pb n="2" facs="Edgeworth_Geneve_33_2_1816_05_06_page02.jpg"/>
                        be said that they wished to<lb/>
                        preserve the arbitrary power<lb/>
                        of dispensing life or death<lb/>
                        but their opinions were brought<lb/>
                        into court - Now the sense<lb/>
                        of the whole nation will<lb/>
                        go with the bill and the<lb/>
                        opposition to it will reflect<lb/>
                        disgrace and odium upon<lb/>
                        the party who brought their<lb/>
                        wretched daily [unclear]wailers[/unclear] to stifle<lb/>
                        reason &amp; humanity -<lb/></p>
                        <p>
                        Alas! .. 60 .. constitutes a<lb/>
                        house of commons when<lb/>
                        the lives &amp; liberties of the<lb/>
                        nation are discussed and<lb/>
                        3 or 400 attend upon an<lb/>
                        alteration in the game laws<lb/></p>
                        
                        <closer>Yours truly<lb/>
                        Rich[superscript]d[/superscript] Lovell Edgeworth<lb/></closer>
                
                
                
            </div>
        </body>
        <back> </back>
